---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Best Shopify Email Marketing Apps for Welcome Series in 2026';
const description = 'A practical comparison of Shopify email apps for welcome flows, preference capture, first-purchase conversion, and responsible onboarding.';
const apps = [['Sequenzy','Simple, intentional onboarding','Good for a concise sequence that sets expectations, teaches the store’s value, and earns the second email without making every welcome a discount.','Validate segmentation depth for complex catalogs and signup sources.','https://sequenzy.com/'],['Klaviyo','Behavioral welcome journeys','Useful for branching on signup source, browsing, category interest, purchase, and customer value.','More setup and a steeper learning curve.','https://www.klaviyo.com/features/marketing-automation'],['Omnisend','Fast ecommerce onboarding','Commerce triggers and templates can shorten the path from signup to useful first purchase across email and SMS.','Template convenience still needs brand and frequency QA.','https://www.omnisend.com/features/automations/'],['Customer.io','Welcome flows with custom event logic','A candidate when signup context, product behavior, support, app activity, and first purchase should change the next message.','Event design, identity mapping, and experimentation require technical ownership.','https://customer.io/'],['Drip','Commerce-first welcome and retention','Useful for product discovery, first-purchase education, complementary products, and second-order follow-up.','Validate catalog and behavioral data depth before building complex branches.','https://www.drip.com/features'],['Sendlane','Stores building visual onboarding flows','Fits welcome, browse, cart, first-order education, review, and reactivation journeys in a visual builder.','Advanced signup-source or support logic may need custom fields.','https://www.sendlane.com/features'],['Brevo','Campaign-led welcome programs','Fits teams that want welcome automation alongside broader campaigns, newsletters, and transactional messages.','Some Shopify behaviors may need connector configuration and clear sending separation.','https://www.brevo.com/features/marketing-automation/'],['Shopify Email','Small stores starting with basics','Native setup keeps a basic welcome program easy to launch for new subscribers and product announcements.','Limited for highly branched onboarding, experimentation, or value-based suppression.','https://www.shopify.com/email-marketing'],['Mailchimp','Brands with an established email workflow','Worth considering when the team already relies on its templates, audiences, and reporting for onboarding.','Test signup-source data, purchase triggers, and automated revenue attribution before choosing it.','https://mailchimp.com/features/marketing-automation/'],['MailerLite','Lean stores publishing useful onboarding content','Good for brand story, product guides, preference questions, and a straightforward first-purchase sequence.','Commerce-specific behavioral triggers are less specialized.','https://www.mailerlite.com/features'],['ActiveCampaign','Welcome programs with sales or service context','Useful when signup leads need qualification, consultations, account stages, or human follow-up alongside automation.','Configuration can be excessive for a simple product catalog.','https://www.activecampaign.com/marketing-automation'],['HubSpot','Brands unifying onboarding and CRM','A candidate for teams needing CRM context, support, sales stages, lifecycle campaigns, and subscriber reporting.','Implementation and total cost can be substantial for smaller stores.','https://www.hubspot.com/products/marketing/marketing-automation'],['Campaign Monitor','Design-led welcome programs','Strong for polished brand introductions, product education, and editorial onboarding where presentation matters.','Evaluate automated behavior and purchase-event coverage before using it for performance flows.','https://www.campaignmonitor.com/features/'],['ConvertKit','Founder-led brands with an editorial voice','Useful for creator notes, educational welcome content, preference capture, and carefully timed first offers.','It is less naturally suited to broad commerce events and deeply branched onboarding.','https://convertkit.com/features']];
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}><main class="container page-stack"><p class="eyebrow">Shopify email marketing apps</p><h1>{title}</h1><p class="lede">A welcome series should make a promise, learn a preference, and help the subscriber decide whether your store deserves attention. It should not be five discount blasts.</p><p>Measure signup-to-purchase rate, second-session rate, unsubscribe rate, and profit after incentives. Include a control or delayed-send test where practical so the team can separate welcome-flow lift from natural new-subscriber intent.</p><h2>Shortlist at a glance</h2><table><thead><tr><th>App</th><th>Best fit</th><th>Strength</th><th>Tradeoff</th></tr></thead><tbody>{apps.map(a=><tr><td>{a[0]}</td><td>{a[1]}</td><td>{a[2]}</td><td>{a[3]}</td></tr>)}</tbody></table>{apps.map(a=><section><h2>{a[0]} for welcome series</h2><p><strong>Best for:</strong> {a[1]}. {a[2]}</p><p><strong>Why it stands out:</strong> A thoughtful series moves from orientation to relevance to decision. {a[0]} is strongest when it lets you change the next message based on category interest, consent, and purchase state. Keep the first email useful even when the subscriber does not buy immediately; that protects trust and improves the quality of later segmentation.</p><table><tbody><tr><th>Pros</th><td>{a[2]}</td></tr><tr><th>Cons</th><td>{a[3]}</td></tr><tr><th>Pricing context</th><td>Check current contacts, sends, automation, and template limits; welcome volume is tied to acquisition activity.</td></tr><tr><th>Source</th><td><a href={a[4]} rel="nofollow">Official product information</a></td></tr></tbody></table></section>)}<h2>Decision guide</h2><table><thead><tr><th>Priority</th><th>Choose based on</th><th>Measure</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Relevance</td><td>Signup and browse data</td><td>Engaged conversion</td></tr><tr><td>Trust</td><td>Preference capture and frequency</td><td>Unsubscribe rate</td></tr><tr><td>Profit</td><td>Incentive and margin controls</td><td>Contribution per subscriber</td></tr></tbody></table><p>Explore <a href="/alternatives">Shopify alternatives</a>, read <a href="/use-cases/welcome-series">welcome-series use cases</a>, or browse <a href="/apps">all Shopify email apps</a>.</p></main></BaseLayout>
